article.headline: Harvard 85, Northeastern 75
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Brian Cusworth scored 20 points and grabbed 14 rebounds, leading Harvard to a 85-75 win over Northeastern on Saturday. Jose Juan Barea paced Northeastern (1-1) with 30 points and seven assists. Shawn James blocked a school record seven shots and scored 18 points for Northeastern. Aaron Davis added 11 points. Harvard (1-2) outscored Northeastern 12-4 in the final 2:13 to close out the win. Kevin Rogus made a pair of 3-pointers to key the run. Janon Cole's jump shot gave Northeastern a 63-61 lead, its first of the game, with 8:05 left. Cusworth's put-back with 3:45 left put Harvard ahead 71-69, and the Crimson never relinquished the lead. Matt Stehle scored 14 points and Rogus 12 for Harvard. Harvard opened the game with a 7-0 run and led 42-34 at halftime. But the Huskies went on a 10-2 run to open the second half, tying the game at 44. Harvard outrebounded the Huskies 43-30 and forced 18 turnovers, leading to 26 points.
